<div id="review_3271607934" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3271607934" />
    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6246246-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546562549p2/6246246.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3271607934?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/6246246-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3271607934" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17714978241646026669">The news reports from Syria have given the world heart breaking pictures of the children who suffer from the civil war. This book has helped to put a face and story to some of those children. Horrifying, vivid descriptions as well as strong, loving friendships creates a memorable fictional story that will keep you up at night wondering why the world has done nothing to help. Zaid and his friends will stay with me for a long time.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


